Mission.Author: Forboding Angel
Mission.Description: We had previously gotten reports of the colony here on Industrial Prime working on some new technology. Turns out that it is a new, compact, supertank. A few of our spies were able to bribe their way to get close enough to the crew of this supertank, and for a hefty sum have agreed to defect.
Mission.Name: Evolution RTS - The Emperor's new Tech

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message
TriggerLogic.Message:
Engineer Marbuk, you have accepted this mission even though the odds are highly stacked against you. You are to be commended for your loyalty and service.
We had previously gotten reports of the colony here on Industrial Prime working on some new technology. Turns out that it is a new, compact, supertank. A few of our spies were able to bribe their way to get close enough to the crew of this supertank, and for a hefty sum have agreed to defect.
There is a slight problem, however. We have no way to airlift the tank out quietly, as it is made of superdense material and our lifters may not be able to clear the tall spires, and going around them is suicide.
This is where you come in, Engineer Marbuk. You are to stealth your way in and rendevous with the supertank and it's crew, Codenamed: Flash
We cannot afford for the enemy to find out that it was we who stole the Flash tank, so we can not afford to allow you to build more than rudimentary powerplants and defenses, radar towers and radar jammers, as anything else, if caught, could be taken as an invasion and would spark an all-out war.
Godspeed, Engineer Marbuk!

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message
TriggerLogic.Message:
You must rendevous with Flash here, then escort them back to the drop zone.
Marbuk must survive Flash must survive

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message
TriggerLogic.Message: It's good to see you, Engineer Marbuk! We are ready to go when you give the word. We need to be careful with what we destroy, as we wouldn't want to trip any alarms. Lead the way!
Bad news, Engineer Marbuk! You have tripped the alarms and alerted the enemy to your presence. I suggest you make your escape as quickly as possible before re-inforcements arrive!

Engineer Marbuk was Killed in Action.
(Hint: Marbuk must survive)

Congratulations Engineer Marbuk! Our technicians cannot wait to see the Flash tank internals to see what makes it tick and apply it to our own designs. You have done your Colony a huge service, Engineer Marbuk, and the council congratulates you on a job well done.
